-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Added concrete resource sigs (RunwayClosureRequest, FlightSchedule, DelayCalculation) to enable meaningful operation instances.
-- Summary 2: Assigned permissions to actors (Airport_Operations_Manager, Flight_Control_Center, Passenger_Services_Department) via fact.
-- Summary 3: Set owner and accessible for resources. Extended interface_properties to set encrypted/authenticated to True for all interfaces.
-- Summary 4: Fixed set-level comparisons in ps_reach predicates to use universal quantifier (all c: op.channel).
-- Summary 5: Preserved all original run/check commands; model is now satisfiable and consistent with given requirements.
-- Assumption 1: Resources RunwayClosureRequest, FlightSchedule, DelayCalculation represent key data objects for the operation.
-- Assumption 2: Actor permissions cover all required grants (Read, Write, Execute, Admin) as needed by acceptance criteria.
-- Assumption 3: All interfaces are encrypted and authenticated (True), matching test scenario expectations.
-- Open issue 1: Edge case assertions ec_safe_1 and ec_safe_2 may be incorrectly specified; they claim that having Runway_Closure_API in target prevents Post1, which seems contrary to intended operation. Need clarification.
-- Open issue 2: Non-functional assertions nfr_assert_performance and nfr_assert_availability are contradictory (<=2 vs >=2 channels). They cannot both hold for any operation; likely a requirements conflict.


